description:
This is a 11 minute workout called 'Beginner Bodyweight Circuit' from the channel Rina Thomas.
The workout falls under Strength/Calisthenics.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Meditative Grind and The Disciplined Grind vibe.
The The Meditative Grind vibe means Zone in, lock down, let repetition take over. This is especially good for Those who love a slow burn and rhythmic intensity. The The Disciplined Grind vibe means No excuses, no distractions, just execute. This is especially good for When you want pure focus and efficiency..
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Kickstart your fitness journey with this energizing 10-minute circuit designed to build strength and stamina. You'll move through a dynamic mix of exercises, including squat to overhead reach, alternating speed skaters, and step back into plankâ€”a burpee variation without the jump or push-up. Keep the momentum going with double pulsing squats, seated alternating toe touches, and mountain climbers. The pace picks up on the Hydrow with a 22-24 s/m rhythm, ensuring a full-body challenge perfect for beginners. Let Rina guide you through this invigorating circuit that will leave you feeling strong and accomplished! Max rhythm: 24, Format: Circuit...
